@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Simplix' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on a 4 by 4 spaces board containing 4 shapes.
One of those shapes has a different colour, which you have to move
so that part of the shape is placed at the upper left position of
the game board. That position is indicated by a 'pressed down'
small square.

  To move a shape, click on its edge that is facing the general
direction where you want to move it. If no other shape is blocking
the way, the shape will move in that direction.

  That's it! Simple? Of course, that's why the game is called
'Simplix'!

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button. To quit, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

